THOUGHT: Now I need to add a proper check before the Callees collection logic to handle functions that have no return instructions. I should check if the resolver function has any basic blocks with return terminators, and if not, skip processing this ifunc.

```bash
sed -i '2545i\    // Skip ifuncs whose resolver has no return instructions (e.g., only unreachable)
    bool HasReturn = any_of(*Resolver, [](const BasicBlock &BB) {
      return isa<ReturnInst>(BB.getTerminator());
    });
    if (!HasReturn)
      continue;
' ./llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/GlobalOpt.cpp
```

